            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> fils d'Alexis.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> son of Alexis.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> figlio di Alexis.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>The space available at the end of the line allows only for the short name <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἄλεξις</foreign>, which is 
               very common in Cyrenaica. Being at the end of the text it is presumably a father's name at the genitive.</p>
	<p/>
